  Summary
===============================================================================

  Metric                    Baseline         MAC4        Improvement
  ------                    --------         ----        -----------
  Total cycles (10 imgs)    43,161,911       15,438,630      -64.2%
  Avg cycles / image         4,316,191        1,543,863      -64.2%
  Accuracy                       10/10            10/10          0
  Overall speedup                   --               --       2.80x

===============================================================================
  Analysis
===============================================================================

  The MAC4 coprocessor achieves a 2.80x overall speedup on end-to-end
  inference.  This covers all three computational stages:

    1. Conv2D layer
       - 3x3 kernel zero-padded to 3 rows of 4 weights
       - 3 MAC4 instructions replace 9 scalar multiply-adds per pixel
       - 4 filters x 26 x 26 output pixels x 3 MAC4 calls = 8,112 MAC4 ops

    2. MaxPool2D layer
       - Scalar comparisons only (no MAC4 benefit)

    3. Fully Connected layer
       - 676 inputs per output neuron, exactly divisible by 4
       - 10 neurons x 169 MAC4 calls = 1,690 MAC4 ops
       - Largest relative benefit: replaces 6,760 scalar MACs

  Total MAC4 instructions per image: 9,802
  Replaced scalar MACs per image:   31,096

  Correctness is preserved: both versions produce identical predictions
  and confidence scores for all 10 test images.

